															<div class="expandable-content">
																<p>
																	Ed and Tum are truly home away from home in honesty, punctuality, passion, talented, destined above all to make your stay above what you could even dream. Rumor has it accommodations are just the icing on the cake to refined perfection. The home is situated next door to Ed and Tum's residence. They will either caravan you around to anything and everything you would like to see, or hand you the key to your home away from home and let you define your own experiences solo. They are a journey outside of the main city, but for me this was ideal. I arrived at the airport where Ed and Tum greeted me and exploration began. If you leave it to those that know there land as well as these two, all you have to do is sit back and enjoy the journey. Before I arrived in Bangkok I had several conversations with Ed and Tum, and in the end it allowed them inside my desires for my experience. In turn the two of them created a itinerary beyond scope. I had to do nothing but show up every morning. Yes you are outside of the city and traffic is shocking but what you gain between the actual accommodations and them makes it all worth it. There is no way I would have experienced half of what I did if left to my own devices. Let me just whisk you away for a moment about detail. Ed and Tum have a little door bell that rings in there home which means " I am ready for breakfast"...moments later the house keeper arrives with the fresh squeezed juice  turns on the tea pot in your kitchen presents you with a selection of teas to choose from should you wish to indulge. While the kettle is coming to a boil, you are lounging at grand twelve person dining room table. All the while the house keeper has returned to the main house to bring over your delicious breakfast. Sipping on juice and reading your menu, yes Chef Tum has hand written you a Good Morning note along with what you will be served. I am vegan so preparing gourmet can be difficult, but with all honestly Tum created masterful dishes that accommodated my dietary needs and palate.  You can look through every listing, but let me make your life easier and make Rumour Has it your number one. If you are traveling solo, or with another and and and have done nothing but express what you hope to get out of your holiday..then your job is done. Let them roll the red carpet out and treat you as if you were the King and Queen of Thailand. The Rumour in (URL HIDDEN) that these two, are the uncrowned King and Queen of the airbnb world. I have stayed many places through airbnb, and you have not stayed WELL in every way until you have allowed yourself to stay at "Rumour Has
																	It" God Speed!
																</p>
