																	Our stay at Rumor Has It was so incredible! Ed and Tum are beautiful hosts--they were so curious about us, where we came from, what our interests were, where we were going--they made us feel at home and comfortable right away. They helped us with taxis, directions into Bangkok and offered suggestions to local restaurants and markets. Apart from Ed and Tum’s hospitality, the Rumor Has It was beyond our expectations. It is charming, artistic and integral to Ed and Tum’s personality. To our delight an wonder, we found out Ed and Tum designed interior and exterior! It is a perfect blend of both personalities. A small river running through their backyard and there is a beautiful white swing my boyfriend and I made use of. It made Ed so happy to see us on it. Tum is a wonderful chef! Each morning she brought out a home made, french-inspired breakfast with delicious cappuccinos and pomegranate juice. We where in heaven!! We felt like the chosen ones! We wish we could have stayed longer, but our trip did not permit. It was the perfect way to end our 6 week backpacking trip across S.E. Asia. Thanks again, Ed and Tum! We will see you again!
